# StackScope Cursor rules — read AGENTS.md first.

## Hard invariants

- Never gate LAYER_BEGIN / LAYER_END on `layer_idx >= 0 and proj is None`.
  Gate them on `is_transformer_block(name)` — the block itself, not any
  descendant that shares the same inferred layer index. Regression:
  tests/python_worker_tests/test_hooks.py.
- Storage is mmap + SQLite. Not MongoDB. Do not add document-store code.
- All event reads go through QueryEngine (C#) or the generated gRPC
  client (Python). Never read the mmap directly from analysis code.
- Every event is addressed by its ULID. Cite ULIDs in diagnostics, never
  positional indices.
- Timestamps: time.perf_counter_ns() on the worker; Stopwatch on C#.
  Never time.time(), datetime.now(), or time.monotonic().
- WPF UI is net8.0-windows only. Do not attempt to compile it on Linux.
  Trust the GitHub Actions canaries.

## Style

- C#: sealed record over class where possible, no `var` in public APIs.
- Python: type hints on all public functions. Compact `if X: return Y`
  guards are allowed (see is_attention_projection); ruff config ignores
  E701/E702 for exactly that.
- XAML: one control per file, follow AnalysisView.xaml layout for new
  analysis panels.
- Never add stubs, mocks, or "TODO: implement later" bodies.

## Environment

- Frontend expects REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL — not applicable to this
  project (there is no web UI). Ignore that pattern.
- Backend does not use MONGO_URL — ignore that too.
- gRPC runs on loopback only. Coordinator picks a free port; workers
  connect back.

## Testing

- Python: STACKSCOPE_SKIP_HF_TESTS=1 PYTHONPATH=workers/inference_worker_py/src
  python3 -m pytest tests/python_worker_tests -q
- .NET Core (works on Linux): dotnet test tests/Core.Tests
- .NET WPF (Windows only): let CI compile.

## Never touch

- proto field numbers. Add new fields with new numbers.
- .git or .emergent directories.
- The Directory.Build.props at the solution root without checking
  every project first.
